Students learn debating skills at bilingual school!
At the bilingual charter school on E. 141st Street, inaugural members of the school’s debate team dedicate their lunch breaks and afternoons to studying current events, vocabulary and rhetoric in English, even though for most, their English language skills are still a work-in-progress. To continue reading click the link below!
Link to article! 



Eight top 10s from New York City’s 2016 test scores
The percentage of New York City students passing their state English tests spiked nearly eight points this year and math pass rates also improved, giving city officials reason to celebrate. It’s worth noting, however, that the average proficiency scores on both exams still hovered below 40 percent. To continue reading this article click the link below!
